Learning stuff from 
http://expressjs.com/4x/api.html

Aim is to build a standalone web app
No mongodb / mongoose dependency
No Jade templating

Mount a few middlewares to the request
Use routes to render static webpages

README
----------------------------------------------------------------------

STEP 1 :
Bring up a web server using express
    a. npm install express
    b. script bin/www -> require('express'), app = express(), app.listen('8088')
    c. node bin/www

STEP 2 :
Render "Hello world" for any request
    a. defined app.get('*', function(req, res){}) to handle any request
    b. request.write is like a buffer
    c. you need to end it with request.end method.

STEP 3 :
Explore Request API. 
get user params (comeon) and query (user)
say "Hello World ${user} from ${param[0]}"
